			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Municipal sludge treatment and disposal;wet sludge  moisture  coontent 70%-75%;drying-incineration</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">市政污泥处理与处置;湿污泥 含水率70%-75%;干化焚烧</baseName>
			</name>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:class level="0">Unit processes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">End-of-life treatment</common:class>
					<common:class level="2">Waste water treatment</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Taking a wastewater treatment plant in Guangzhou as an example, the daily sewage treatment capacity of the plant is 250,000 t/d, and the daily output of wet sludge after mechanical compression is 90 t/d. It is assumed that the plant is equipped with a low-pressure small bubbling fluidized bed boiler for sludge reduction and harmless incineration.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">以广州市某污水处理厂为研究实例，该厂的污水日处理能力为 250000ｔ/d， 机械压缩后湿污泥日产量 90ｔ/d。假定厂内配套低压小型鼓泡流化床锅炉进行污泥减量化、无害化焚烧处理。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
		<quantitativeReference type="Reference flow(s)">
			<functionalUnitOrOther xml:lang="en"> The life cycle study boundary starts from the wet sludge (moisture content is about 70% ~ 75%) after mechanical compression and dewatering in the sewage treatment plant to the final disposal functional unit adopts 1t wet sludge after mechanical compression. </functionalUnitOrOther>
			<referenceToReferenceFlow>8</referenceToReferenceFlow>
		</quantitativeReference>
		<time/>
		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="GZ-GD-CN"/>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">The system uses hollow paddle technology for sludge drying, and the saturated steam (0.4MPa, 150°C) produced by the incinerator is used as the dry heat source of the sludge, reducing the moisture content of the wet sludge from 70.5% to about 40%, and then blending with coal for incineration. The combined process can achieve self-equilibrium of energy, drying 90t/day wet sludge requires a boiler steam volume of 3.6t/h, a boiler exhaust gas temperature of 160°C, and a boiler efficiency of 72.82%. In order to meet the heat balance, 7.65t/day of anthracite needs to be blended.</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">系统采用空心桨叶技术进行污泥干燥处理，焚烧炉产生的饱和蒸汽 （0.4MPa、150℃ ）为污泥的干燥热源，将湿污泥含水率从70.5％降至 40％左右，然后与煤掺混进行焚烧处理。该联合工艺可以达到能量的自平衡，干燥 90ｔ/天的湿污泥需要锅炉蒸汽量 3．6ｔ/h，锅炉排烟温度 160℃，锅炉效率为 72.82％。为满足热量平衡，需要掺烧无烟煤 7．65ｔ/天。</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The described industrial process is intended for the treatment and final disposal of municipal sludge with a moisture content of 70%-75%. This entails mechanical compression for dewatering followed by drying and incineration. The process is used within facilities that manage waste from sewage treatment plants, converting high-moisture sludge into a reduced volume of ash suitable for final disposal. Applicable in scenarios where waste management protocols demand the reduction of sludge volume and the mitigation of potential environmental impacts.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">该工业过程用于处理和处置含水率为70%-75%的市政污泥。过程包括机械压缩脱水以及随后的干化和焚烧。此过程适用于管理污水处理厂废物的设施，将高含水污泥转换为体积更小的灰烬，以便最终处置。适用于需要减少污泥体积并减轻潜在环境影响的废物管理协议场景。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="71898ccf-9ef9-93cd-e4c3-be59b573caa3" uri="../sources/71898ccf-9ef9-93cd-e4c3-be59b573caa3.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">QKXMbzhOTonI4XxY5cbcvivmn1b.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
